trans-unit.source: Applies To: Azure AD Graph API
trans-unit.target: Applies To: Azure AD Graph API

trans-unit.source: Represents an Azure Active Directory group.
trans-unit.target: Represents an Azure Active Directory group.

trans-unit.source: This topic provides descriptions of the declared properties and navigation properties of the <system>Group</system> entity, as well as the operations, actions, and functions that can be called on a group.
trans-unit.target: This topic provides descriptions of the declared properties and navigation properties of the <system>Group</system> entity, as well as the operations, actions, and functions that can be called on a group.

trans-unit.source: The <system>Group</system> entity type has the following properties:
trans-unit.target: The <system>Group</system> entity type has the following properties:

trans-unit.source: An optional description for the group.
trans-unit.target: An optional description for the group.

trans-unit.source: Indicates whether this object was synced from the on-premises directory.
trans-unit.target: Indicates whether this object was synced from the on-premises directory.

trans-unit.source: The display name for the group.
trans-unit.target: The display name for the group.

trans-unit.source: This property is required when a group is created and it cannot be cleared during updates.
trans-unit.target: This property is required when a group is created and it cannot be cleared during updates.

trans-unit.source: Indicates the last time at which the object was synced with the on-premises directory.
trans-unit.target: Indicates the last time at which the object was synced with the on-premises directory.

trans-unit.source: The SMTP address for the group, for example, "serviceadmins@contoso.onmicrosoft.com".
trans-unit.target: The SMTP address for the group, for example, "serviceadmins@contoso.onmicrosoft.com".

trans-unit.source: Specifies whether the group is mail-enabled.
trans-unit.target: Specifies whether the group is mail-enabled.

trans-unit.source: If the <embeddedLabel>securityEnabled</embeddedLabel> property is also <languageKeyword>true</languageKeyword>, the group is a mail-enabled security group; otherwise, the group is a Microsoft Exchange distribution group.
trans-unit.target: If the <embeddedLabel>securityEnabled</embeddedLabel> property is also <languageKeyword>true</languageKeyword>, the group is a mail-enabled security group; otherwise, the group is a Microsoft Exchange distribution group.

trans-unit.source: Only (pure) security groups can be created using Azure AD Graph.
trans-unit.target: Only (pure) security groups can be created using Azure AD Graph.

trans-unit.source: For this reason, the property must be set <languageKeyword>false</languageKeyword> when creating a group and it cannot be updated using Azure AD Graph.
trans-unit.target: For this reason, the property must be set <languageKeyword>false</languageKeyword> when creating a group and it cannot be updated using Azure AD Graph.

trans-unit.source: The mail alias for the group.
trans-unit.target: The mail alias for the group.

trans-unit.source: This property must be specified when a group is created.
trans-unit.target: This property must be specified when a group is created.

trans-unit.source: The unique identifier for the group.
trans-unit.target: The unique identifier for the group.

trans-unit.source: A string that identifies the object type.
trans-unit.target: A string that identifies the object type.

trans-unit.source: For groups the value is always “Group”.
trans-unit.target: For groups the value is always “Group”.

trans-unit.source: Contains the on-premises security identifier (SID) for the group that was synchronized from on-premises to the cloud.
trans-unit.target: Contains the on-premises security identifier (SID) for the group that was synchronized from on-premises to the cloud.

trans-unit.source: A collection of error details that are preventing this group from being provisioned successfully.
trans-unit.target: A collection of error details that are preventing this group from being provisioned successfully.

trans-unit.source: Specifies whether the group is a security group.
trans-unit.target: Specifies whether the group is a security group.

trans-unit.source: If the mailEnabled property is also true, the group is a mail-enabled security group; otherwise it is a security group.
trans-unit.target: If the mailEnabled property is also true, the group is a mail-enabled security group; otherwise it is a security group.

trans-unit.source: Only (pure) security groups can be created using Azure AD Graph.
trans-unit.target: Only (pure) security groups can be created using Azure AD Graph.

trans-unit.source: For this reason, the property must be set <languageKeyword>true</languageKeyword> when creating a group.
trans-unit.target: For this reason, the property must be set <languageKeyword>true</languageKeyword> when creating a group.

trans-unit.source: (Only Contact, Group, and User objects are supported)
trans-unit.target: (Only Contact, Group, and User objects are supported)

trans-unit.source: Users, contacts, and groups that are members of this group.
trans-unit.target: Users, contacts, and groups that are members of this group.

trans-unit.source: HTTP Methods: GET (supported for all groups), POST (supported for security groups and mail-enabled security groups), DELETE (supported only for security groups)
trans-unit.target: HTTP Methods: GET (supported for all groups), POST (supported for security groups and mail-enabled security groups), DELETE (supported only for security groups)

trans-unit.source: Groups that this group is a member of.
trans-unit.target: Groups that this group is a member of.

trans-unit.source: HTTP Methods: GET (supported for all groups)
trans-unit.target: HTTP Methods: GET (supported for all groups)

trans-unit.source: The owners are a set of non-admin users who are allowed to modify this object.
trans-unit.target: The owners are a set of non-admin users who are allowed to modify this object.

trans-unit.source: Contains the set of applications that a group is assigned to.
trans-unit.target: Contains the set of applications that a group is assigned to.

trans-unit.source: Contains the extension properties associated with the application.
trans-unit.target: Contains the extension properties associated with the application.

trans-unit.source: There are three kinds of groups: mail distribution groups (<embeddedLabel>mailEnabled</embeddedLabel> property <languageKeyword>true</languageKeyword> and <embeddedLabel>securityEnabled</embeddedLabel> property <languageKeyword>false</languageKeyword>); mail-enabled security groups (<embeddedLabel>mailEnabled</embeddedLabel> property <languageKeyword>true</languageKeyword> and <embeddedLabel>securityEnabled</embeddedLabel> property <languageKeyword>true</languageKeyword>); and, (pure) security groups (<embeddedLabel>mailEnabled</embeddedLabel> property <languageKeyword>false</languageKeyword> and <embeddedLabel>securityEnabled</embeddedLabel> property <languageKeyword>true</languageKeyword>).
trans-unit.target: There are three kinds of groups: mail distribution groups (<embeddedLabel>mailEnabled</embeddedLabel> property <languageKeyword>true</languageKeyword> and <embeddedLabel>securityEnabled</embeddedLabel> property <languageKeyword>false</languageKeyword>); mail-enabled security groups (<embeddedLabel>mailEnabled</embeddedLabel> property <languageKeyword>true</languageKeyword> and <embeddedLabel>securityEnabled</embeddedLabel> property <languageKeyword>true</languageKeyword>); and, (pure) security groups (<embeddedLabel>mailEnabled</embeddedLabel> property <languageKeyword>false</languageKeyword> and <embeddedLabel>securityEnabled</embeddedLabel> property <languageKeyword>true</languageKeyword>).

trans-unit.source: You can only create security groups using Azure AD Graph (you cannot create mail-enabled security groups or mail distribution groups).
trans-unit.target: You can only create security groups using Azure AD Graph (you cannot create mail-enabled security groups or mail distribution groups).

trans-unit.source: For this reason the <embeddedLabel>mailEnabled</embeddedLabel> property must be set <languageKeyword>false</languageKeyword> and the <embeddedLabel>securityEnabled</embeddedLabel> property must be set <languageKeyword>true</languageKeyword> when creating a group.
trans-unit.target: For this reason the <embeddedLabel>mailEnabled</embeddedLabel> property must be set <languageKeyword>false</languageKeyword> and the <embeddedLabel>securityEnabled</embeddedLabel> property must be set <languageKeyword>true</languageKeyword> when creating a group.

trans-unit.source: All properties marked required must be specified when creating a security group using Azure AD Graph.
trans-unit.target: All properties marked required must be specified when creating a security group using Azure AD Graph.

trans-unit.source: You cannot update a group from a security group to a mail-enabled security group or to a mail distribution group using Azure AD Graph.
trans-unit.target: You cannot update a group from a security group to a mail-enabled security group or to a mail distribution group using Azure AD Graph.
